<paragraph id="8628475BFFB58506FF13F826FA63F78B" blockId="18.[136,1452,1972,2071]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB58506FF13F826FEE9F86E" bold="true" box="[189,294,2008,2034]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">Notes:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFB58506FE88F827FE61F86E" author="Luer, C. A." box="[294,430,2008,2035]" pageId="18" pageNumber="229" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref30080" refString="Luer, C. A. (2009) Miscellaneous new species in Pleurothallidinae (Orchidaceae). Selbyana 30: 1 - 71." type="journal article" year="2009">Luer (2009)</bibRefCitation>
described the narrow, needle-like leaves of this species as unique in the genus. However, similar leaves are now also known to be found in 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB58506FD16F803FC8DF78A" authorityName="Pupulin, Bogarin &amp; Fernandez" authorityYear="2010" box="[696,834,2045,2070]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="18" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sotoanus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB58506FD16F803FC8DF78A" box="[696,834,2045,2070]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">M. sotoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described in 2010 (
<figureCitation id="1EAC5BDEFFB58506FB89F802FB4DF78B" box="[1063,1154,2044,2071]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,190,1853]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Leaf variation in Myoxanthus species.A. Myoxanthus cereus. B. M. parahybunensis. C. M. colothrix. D. M. hirsuticaulis. E. M. congestus. F. M. trachychlamys. G. M. sotoanus. H. M. scandens. Scale bar = 5 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5425743/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="229">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
). This species is similar to
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFFB48507FF26FF61FF19FF40" blockId="19.[136,1451,158,220]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB48507FF26FF61FEDAFF24" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[136,277,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB48507FF26FF61FEDAFF24" box="[136,277,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB48507FEE5FF61FE2BFF24" authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[331,484,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB48507FEE5FF61FE2BFF24" box="[331,484,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB48507FDB3FF61FD02FF24" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="2009" box="[541,717,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aciculifolius">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB48507FDB3FF61FD02FF24" box="[541,717,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. aciculifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the long-ciliate margins of the middle lobe of the lip.
</paragraph>
